I need to identify the line item representing profit after all expenses are deducted, along with 5 key components used in its calculation.

Looking at the income statement, I can see that "Net Profit" is the final profit figure after all deductions. The value shown is -1669849.77.

For the sub-items that contribute to this calculation, I'll identify 5 key components:

1. Total Revenue: 6920513.79 - This is the starting point of the income statement
2. Cost of Goods Sold: 5580000.00 - Direct costs associated with producing goods
3. Total Expenses: 2666904.55 - All operating expenses combined
4. Interest Income: 2566.71 - A positive contribution to profit
5. Tax Expense: 346025.72 - The final deduction before arriving at net profit

The calculation flows as follows:
- Revenue minus Cost of Goods Sold gives Gross Profit
- Gross Profit minus Total Expenses plus Interest Income gives Profit Before Tax
- Profit Before Tax minus Tax Expense gives Net Profit
